'''Miwa Shrine''' (美和神社) refers to multiple [[Shinto shrines]] with the name "Miwa."
* {{ill|Miwa Shrine (Kiryū)|ja|美和神社 (桐生市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (Miyamoto Town, [[Kiryū City]], [[Gunma Prefecture]]) - A [[Shikinai-sha]] of [[Yamato District]], [[Kōzuke Province]]. * {{ill|Miwa Shrine (Fuefuki City)|ja|美和神社 (笛吹市)|1=Miwa Shrine (Fuefuki City)|12=draft|12=draft}} ([[Misaka Town]], [[Fuefuki City]], [[Yamanashi Prefecture]]) - A [[Kokushi Genzaisha]] of [[Kai Province]]. * {{ill|Miwa Shrine (Nagano)|ja|美和神社 (長野市)|12=draft|12=draft}} ([[Miwa]], [[Nagano City]], [[Nagano Prefecture]]) - A [[Shikinai-sha]] of [[Mizunai District]], [[Shinano Province]]. * {{ill|Miwa Shrine (Setouchi, Higashisue)|ja|美和神社 (瀬戸内市長船町東須恵)|12=draft|12=draft}} ([[Higashisue]], [[Osafune Town]], [[Setouchi City]], [[Okayama Prefecture]]) - A [[Shikinai-sha]] of [[Oku District]], [[Bizen Province]]. * {{ill|Miwa Shrine (Setouchi, Fukusato)|ja|美和神社 (瀬戸内市長船町福里)|12=draft|12=draft}} (Fukusato, Osafune Town, Setouchi City, Okayama Prefecture) - A reference site for the above Shikinai-sha. == See Also == * [[Ōmiwa Shrines]] * [[Miwa Shrines]] * {{ill|Mitsutorii|ja|三ツ鳥居|12=draft|12=draft}}
